Comet Halley orbits the sun every 75 yea.content:
Bill’s second sight occurs when his age B2 = 3 × 30 = 90. The comet returns every 75 years, so the interval between Bill’s two sightings is a multiple of 75: B2 − B1 = 75k for some positive integer k. Then B1 = 90 − 75k. To keep B1 nonnegative, k = 1, giving B1 = 15. 

Thus, Bill was 15 when he saw the comet for the first time. 

\boxed{15}

Regina wrote 9 novels last year. If this.content:
Let x be the number of novels written this year. Given that 3/4 of x equals 9:
x = 9 ÷ (3/4) = 9 × (4/3) = 12.
So this year she has written 12 novels. \boxed{12}

